-forgiveness-al-maghfirah","tag-greetings-al-tahyah","tag-islam","tag-manners-adab","tag-monotheism-tawhid","tag-pardon-al-afwa","tag-shaking-hands-al-musahafah"],"aioseo_notices":[],"jetpack_featured_media_url":"","jetpack_shortlink":"https:\/\/wp.me\/p95VHY-1uV","jetpack_sharing_enabled":true,"jetpack-related-posts":[{"id":17061,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/11\/30\/greetings-shake-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":5761,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Best to shake hands, not bow or kiss","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 30, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: A man said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, when a man among us meets his brother or friend, should he bow for him?\u201d The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cNo.\u201d The man said, \u201cShould he embrace him and kiss him?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cNo.\u201d\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32231,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/fall-like-leaves-shaking-hands\/","url_meta":{"origin":5761,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Sins expiated by shaking hands","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, when the Muslim shakes hands with his brother, both of their sins fall away like the falling of leaves from a tree.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 8335 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi (authentic due to external evidence)\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u063