:3},"title":"Hadith on Rahmah: The Prophet more merciful to us than ourselves","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 21, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Umaymah bint Ruqayqah reported: I pledged allegiance to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, with a group of women. The Prophet said to us, \u201cIn so far as you are able and capable.\u201d I said, \u201cAllah and his messenger are more merciful to us than we\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":32229,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/16\/shaking-hands-hugging-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":5761,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Greetings: Shaking hands, hugging after long journey","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 16, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: If the companions of the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, met each other, they would shake hands. If they had returned from a journey, they would embrace each other. Source: al-Mu\u2019jam al-Awsat\u0323 lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 97 Grade: Jayyid (very good) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0643\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0635\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0627\u0628\u064f\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19804,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/08\/28\/shaking-hands-expiate-sins\/","url_meta":{"orig